#compdef termdbms
# =============================================================================
# termdbms — Matt Athey's "TUI for viewing and editing database files."
#             A bubbletea-based terminal database client supporting
#             both SQLite (via the modernc.org/sqlite pure-Go driver,
#             zero CGo) and MySQL.  Renders database schemas + tables
#             + row data in a full-screen TUI with lipgloss-styled
#             panels, vim-like navigation (h/j/k/l for cell movement,
#             /  for search, : for command-mode), inline cell editing,
#             SQL query execution, theme selection (default/Solarized/
#             Dracula/Catppuccin), and ASCII-only fallback for
#             terminals without ANSI support.  Designed as an
#             alternative to GUI database tools (DBeaver, TablePlus,
#             pgAdmin) for users who prefer terminal workflows + vim
#             muscle memory + low-resource overhead.
#
# Author:  Matt Athey (@mathaou) — independent Go developer who
#          created termdbms in 2021 as a personal SQLite explorer.
#          Active maintainer.
# Source:  https://github.com/mathaou/termdbms
# CLI:     main.go (uses Go stdlib `flag` package for argv parsing
#                    + bubbletea + lipgloss for the visible TUI)
# Library: charmbracelet/lipgloss
#          ("Style definitions for nice terminal layouts 👄" —
#           Charm's CSS-like styling DSL for terminal applications.
#           lipgloss is the SECOND Charmbracelet library documented
#           in the Go ecosystem alongside bubbletea R531 and huh
#           R543 — the THIRD Charmbracelet library in the taxonomy.)
# License: MIT
# Status:  Active — 1811+ stars on mathaou/termdbms; lipgloss
#          itself is 11353+ stars on charmbracelet/lipgloss
#          (continuous development since 2021 by the Charm team).
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
